<li id="cite_note-Ramsey-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Ramsey_8-0">^</a></b> Title:The languages of China, Author:S. Robert Ramsey, Publisher:Princeton University Press, 1987, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0691066949" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 0691066949</a>, 9780691066943, chapter 1.</li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9">^</a></b> Original text in Chinese: "<span lang="zh" xml:lang="zh">普通话就是现代汉民族共同语，是全国各民族通用的语言。普通话以北京语音为标准音，以北方话为基础方言，以典范的现代白话文著作语法规范</span>"</li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10">^</a></b> <span class="citation web">Standing Committee on Language Education &amp; Research (2006-03-25) <a href="http://archive.news.gov.hk/isd/ebulletin/en/category/atschool/060325/html/060325en02002.htm" class="external text" rel="nofollow">"Putonghua promotion stepped up"</a> Hong Kong Government <span class="printonly"><a href="http://archive.news.gov.hk/isd/ebulletin/en/category/atschool/060325/html/060325en02002.htm" class="external free" rel="nofollow">http://archive.news.gov.hk/isd/ebulletin/en/category/atschool/060325/html/060325en02002.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved 2011-02-12</span></span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Putonghua+promotion+stepped+up&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Standing+Committee+on+Language+Education+%26+Research&amp;rft.au=Standing+Committee+on+Language+Education+%26+Research&amp;rft.date=2006-03-25&amp;rft.pub=Hong+Kong+Government&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Farchive.news.gov.hk%2Fisd%2Febulletin%2Fen%2Fcategory%2Fatschool%2F060325%2Fhtml%2F060325en02002.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Standard_Chinese"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11">^</a></b> <span class="citation web">Hong Kong Police <a href="http://www.police.gov.hk/offbeat/692/0110_e.htm" class="external text" rel="nofollow">"Online training to boost Chinese skills"</a> Hong Kong Government <span class="printonly"><a href="http://www.police.gov.hk/offbeat/692/0110_e.htm" class="external free" rel="nofollow">http://www.police.gov.hk/offbeat/692/0110_e.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved 2011-02-12</span></span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Online+training+to+boost+Chinese+skills&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Hong+Kong+Police&amp;rft.au=Hong+Kong+Police&amp;rft.pub=Hong+Kong+Government&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.police.gov.hk%2Foffbeat%2F692%2F0110_e.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Standard_Chinese"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
